"{\"uid\": \"finanznachrichten.de-nachrichten-2024-04-61854287-social-impact-partners-sip-brain-health-innovation-olympics-awards-global-student-teams-in-intergenerational-competition-296.htm\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Boston, Massachusetts--(Newsfile Corp. - April 3, 2024) - Social Impact Partners is proud to announce the successful conclusion of the 2nd Season of the Brain Health Innovation Olympics, focused on defining criteria and developing ideas to build and implement Brain Health Centers of Excellence.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This season's competition brought together teams from prestigious institutions worldwide, including Dartmouth College, Asian Institute of Management, Indian Institute of Management - Lucknow, Rotman School of Management, SDA Bocconi, and the University of Calgary.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dartmouth_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1550101305202283e-17, \"text\": \"Dartmouth College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dartmouth_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dartmouth_College\"}, {\"begin\": 522, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bocconi_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bocconi\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bocconi_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bocconi_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Representing four continents and 10 countries, these teams engaged in an intense 8-week program guided by the expertise of the IXL Center team and a distinguished group of executive leaders.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Jones_IXL\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.442388167142737e-21, \"text\": \"IXL\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Jones_IXL\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Jones_IXL\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Participating students from colleges and universities around the world joined SIP's Brain Health Innovation Olympics challenge to create Brain Health Centers of Excellence.To view an enhanced version of this graphic, please visit:https://images.newsfilecorp.com/files/10060/204134_slide6.jpg  \\\"We are in a unique moment post-pandemic, where the entire world is focused on brain health.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 832, \"end\": 835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\", \"score\": 0.7435067250250308, \"rank\": 0.2590544318819752, \"text\": \"SIP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2nd season of the Innovation Olympics has been a testament to the power of multi-sectoral and inter-generational collaboration and innovation of a younger generation,\\\" said Sarah Hoit, Co-Founder and Chairman of Social Impact Partners.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"score\": 0.8980147213733689, \"rank\": 0.11307881822408028, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\"}, {\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Impact Partners\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning concepts include fully integrated solutions to deliverBrain Health Centers of Excellencein Senior Living Communities, Brain Health incubators and investment funds, workplace brain health programs, and increased caregiver support.\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All plans emphasized the critical role of Food as Medicine, the need for integrated innovative technologies, and the power of collaboration in the solutions.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Student innovations and executive leaders focused on developing the criteria and implementation strategy for Brain Health Centers of Excellence in senior living, as well as campuses, colleges, and universities.To view an enhanced version of this graphic, please visit:https://images.newsfilecorp.com/files/10060/204134_slide7.jpg  \\\"This season's focus on the design and implementation of Brain Health Centers of Excellence in Senior Living facilities and Academic institutions provide a cohesive platform to better address the lack of brain care across the lifespan.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The diverse perspectives and expertise brought by the participating teams and judges have laid a solid foundation for future advances,\\\" said Dr. Gene Bowman, Instructor in Neurology at Harvard Medical School and Director of the McCance Center for Brain Health Clinical Trials Unit at Massachusetts General Hospital.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2495, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Bowman\", \"score\": 0.636073744458788, \"rank\": 0.5720673898491591, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Bowman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Division_of_Bowman\"}, {\"begin\": 2530, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_Medical_School\", \"score\": 0.9999999485894491, \"rank\": 5.141037180532949e-08, \"text\": \"Harvard Medical School\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_Medical_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_Medical_School\"}, {\"begin\": 2629, \"end\": 2659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Massachusetts General Hospital\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Massachusetts_General_Hospital\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 40 leaders from corporate, nonprofit, science, and technology sectors who are part of the SIP's Global Brain Health and Longevity Initiative collaborated to judge the Olympics and mentor the students, and they will continue to work together to bring these ideas to the marketplace.\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2757, \"end\": 2760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\", \"score\": 0.7435067250250308, \"rank\": 0.2590544318819752, \"text\": \"SIP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\"}, {\"begin\": 2787, \"end\": 2796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Longevity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.07448175692682e-38, \"text\": \"Longevity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Longevity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Longevity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2024 Judge PanelTo view an enhanced version of this graphic, please visit:https://images.newsfilecorp.com/files/10060/204134_slide3.jpg  \\\"The results of the Innovation Olympics are powerful.\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 3140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We look forward to incorporating these concepts into our work as we partner with SIP to bring innovation and impact to this critical topic,\\\" said Marc Plumart, Chief Growth and Commercial Officer at Sodexo, the world's leader in sustainable food and valued experiences, serving more than 100 million people daily in 53 countries.\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3340, \"end\": 3346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2nd Season of the Brain Health Innovation Olympics represents a significant step forward in advancing brain health initiatives globally.\", \"from\": 3472, \"to\": 3612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Social Impact Partners looks forward to continuing this momentum and driving further innovation in the coming seasons.\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3620, \"end\": 3635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Impact Partners\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information about Social Impact Partners and the Brain Health Innovation Olympics, please visit www.socialimpact.partners and join SIP's Global Brain Health and Longevity Initiative.\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3767, \"end\": 3782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Impact Partners\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Impact_Partners\"}, {\"begin\": 3873, \"end\": 3876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gruppo_TIM\", \"score\": 0.7435067250250308, \"rank\